    * Per capita: $1,668 &#91;5&#93;, placing it at [186th](/List_of_countries_by_GDP_(PPP)_per_capita), a stark indicator of the economic challenges.
* (nominal) 2023 estimate:
    * Total: $13.176 billion &#91;5&#93;, ranking [149th](/List_of_countries_by_GDP_(nominal)).
    * Per capita: $579 &#91;5&#93;, placing it at [190th](/List_of_countries_by_GDP_(nominal)_per_capita), further underscoring the severe economic constraints faced by the average [Malawian](/Demographics_of_Malawi).

The [Gini coefficient](/Gini_coefficient) (2016) stood at 44.7 &#91;6&#93;, indicating a medium level of inequality within the nation, a common affliction in developing economies.

Its [Human Development Index](/Human_Development_Index) (HDI) (2023) is 0.517 &#91;7&#93;, categorized as low, placing it at [172nd](/List_of_countries_by_Human_Development_Index), a clear sign of significant developmental hurdles.

The national [currency](/Currency) is the [Malawian kwacha](/Malawian_kwacha) (D) ([MWK](/ISO_4217)).

